//listing of all techniques and passes with embedded asm listings 

technique MainTec
{
    pass DrawObject
    {
        vertexshader = 
            asm {
            
//
            // Generated by Microsoft (R) HLSL Shader Compiler 9.29.952.3111
            //
            // Parameters:
            //
            //   float4x4 WorldMatrix;
            //   float4x4 WorldViewProjMatrix;
            //
            //
            // Registers:
            //
            //   Name                Reg   Size
            //   ------------------- ----- ----
            //   WorldViewProjMatrix c0       4
            //   WorldMatrix         c4       3
            //
            
                vs_2_0
                def c7, 0, 1, 0, 0
                dcl_position v0
                dcl_normal v1
                dcl_texcoord v2
                dp4 oPos.x, v0, c0
                dp4 oPos.y, v0, c1
                dp4 oPos.z, v0, c2
                dp4 oPos.w, v0, c3
                dp3 r0.x, v1, c4
                dp3 r0.y, v1, c5
                dp3 r0.z, v1, c6
                dp3 r0.w, r0, r0
                rsq r0.w, r0.w
                mul oT2.xyz, r0.w, r0
                mov oT1.xy, v2
                mov oT3.xyz, c7.x
                mov oD0, c7.y
            
            // approximately 13 instruction slots used
            
};

        pixelshader = 
            asm {
            
//
            // Generated by Microsoft (R) HLSL Shader Compiler 9.29.952.3111
            //
            // Parameters:
            //
            //   sampler2D ObjTexSampler;
            //   bool use_texture;
            //
            //
            // Registers:
            //
            //   Name          Reg   Size
            //   ------------- ----- ----
            //   use_texture   c0       1
            //   ObjTexSampler s0       1
            //
            
                ps_2_0
                dcl t1.xy
                dcl v0
                dcl_2d s0
                texld r0, t1, s0
                mul r0, r0, v0
                cmp r0, -c0.x, v0, r0
                mov oC0, r0
            
            // approximately 4 instruction slots used (1 texture, 3 arithmetic)
            
};
    }
}
